    <briefdescription>
<para>TCP socket port interface — implement these for your platform. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Minimal BSD-like socket abstraction for TCP client connections. Higher-level modules (HTTP client, MQTT, OTA) use this interface without knowing the underlying TCP/IP stack.</para>
<para>Implement these functions by wrapping your platform&apos;s socket API:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>lwIP (raw or socket mode)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>ESP-IDF (POSIX sockets via lwIP)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>POSIX (Linux/macOS for development)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Vendor TCP/IP stack</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
